Package com.lugowoy.helper.filling.array

Interface FillingArray<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of data objects stored and filled into an array.
    All Superinterfaces:
    Filling<Array<T>>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    FillingArrayNumbers<T>, FillingArrayPoints<T>, FillingArrayStrings
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    FillingArrayPointsRandomDoubleNumbers, FillingArrayPointsRandomIntegerNumbers, FillingArrayPointsReadDoubleNumbers, FillingArrayPointsReadIntegerNumbers, FillingArrayPointsReadValues, FillingArrayRandomDoubleNumbers, FillingArrayRandomIntegerNumbers, FillingArrayRandomLengthValueStrings, FillingArrayRandomStrings, FillingArrayRandomValueStrings, FillingArrayReadDoubleNumbers, FillingArrayReadingValueStrings, FillingArrayReadIntegerNumbers, FillingArrayReadValues, FillingArraySequentialAscendingDecimalDigitOfDoubleNumbers, FillingArraySequentialAscendingDoubleNumbers, FillingArraySequentialAscendingIntegerNumbers, FillingArraySequentialDescendingDecimalDigitOfDoubleNumbers, FillingArraySequentialDescendingDoubleNumbers, FillingArraySequentialDescendingIntegerNumbers
    public interface FillingArray<T>
extends Filling<Array<T>>
    The interface that declares a contract to filling an array with data.

    Also this interface is the inheritor of the Filling interface and thereby redefines its contract for filling with data of an object of the Array class and classical arrays.

    Created by Konstantin Lugowoy on 08-Jan-18.

    Version:
    1.2
    Author:
    Konstantin Lugowoy
